          "t": "h",
          "tag": "h3",
          "text": "2012 - Pakistan"
        },
        {
          "t": "h",
          "tag": "h3",
          "text": "Technology, Information, and the Internet"
        },
        {
          "t": "h",
          "tag": "h3",
          "text": "Over 10,000 employees"
        },
        {
          "t": "h",
          "tag": "h2",
          "text": "The Customer"
        },
        {
          "t": "p",
          "text": "Daraz is the leading online marketplace across South Asia (excluding India). Daraz provides access to 10 million products and delivers more than 2 million packages every month. In 2018, Daraz was acquired by Alibaba Group. The business covers four key areas – e-commerce, logistics, payment infrastructure, and financial services – providing sellers and customers with an end-to-end commerce solution. With access to over 500 million customers in various markets, Daraz strives to deliver on its promise of enabling easy access to a wide assortment of products. Together with its digitalized logistics business, it employs more than 10,000 people, helping to bring economic opportunities to communities in South Asia."
        },
        {
          "t": "img",
          "src": "https://azure.folio3.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/daraz_logo-2.png",
          "w": 267,
          "h": 267,
          "alt": ""
        }
      ],
